=head1 NAME

Lingua::JA::Name::Splitter - split a Japanese name into given and family name

=head1 SYNOPSIS

    use Lingua::JA::Name::Splitter 'split_name';
    my ($family, $given) = split_name ('風太郎');
    # Now $family = 風 and $given = 太郎.

=head1 FUNCTIONS

=head2 split_name

    my ($family, $given) = split_name ('渡辺純子');

This splits the name using some heuristics.

